<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="wind-v">wind <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /waɪnd/    美 /waɪnd/  </p>
<p>(wound, wound)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>卷绕；缠绕：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>wind a bandage firmly around the wounded leg 
用绷带紧紧地裹住受伤的腿</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>上紧...的发条：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You must wind this clock once a day. 
你得每天给这个钟上一次发条。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>(道路、河流等) 弯曲；蜿蜒：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The river winds to the sea. 
这条河蜿蜒流向大海。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Highway 90 <strong>winds its way along</strong> the coast.
90号高速公路沿着海岸线蜿蜒而去。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="wind-up">wind up</h3>
<p>1.<strong>给（机械）上发条；使（活动、会议等）结束：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Mark wanted to wind the meeting up quickly because he had a plane to catch.
马克想快点结束会议，因为他要赶飞机。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">派生词汇</h2>
<p>winding  /winding/ adj   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a winding path
蜿蜒的小路</p></div></div>